’; Standen in Benenden and Standen in Biddenden (Kent) derive from Old English <i>stānig</i> ‘stony, rocky’ + <i>denn</i>; Standen in Hawkinge (Kent) derives from Old English <i>stān</i> + <i>denn</i>; the Berkshire, Devon, Hertfordshire, Isle of Wight, and Staffordshire placenames derive from Old English <i>stān</i> + <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’."]}]},{"name":"Adam","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: The Scripture name, in Hebrew, Adham, signifying 'man;' literally earthy, red earth; Rudolph, however, says the name in Ethiopic means ' to be fair, beautiful.' Hence the nurse-name Addy, little Adam."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Adam De Standon was born in 1150, in Trentham, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Adam de Standon before 1172, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1181, in Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 31."},"et":{"1150–1181":"1150–1181","1148–1181":"1148–1181","1172–1208":"1172–1208","1148":"1148","before 1172":"enne 1172","1150":"1150","1172":"1172","1181":"1181","1208":"1208","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Trentham, Staffordshire, England":"Trentham, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Trentham Court, Staffordshire, England":"Trentham, Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"1150–1181":"1150–1181","1148–1181":"1148–1181","1172–1208":"1172–1208","1148":"1148","before 1172":"ennen vuotta 1172","1150":"1150","1172":"1172","1181":"1181","1208":"1208","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Trentham, Staffordshire, England":"Trentham, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Trentham Court, Staffordshire, England":"Trentham, Staffordshire, England"},"fr":{"1150–1181":"1150–1181","1148–1181":"1148–1181","1172–1208":"1172–1208","1148":"1148","before